  "target_response": {
    "text": "Sleep performance is just a ratio: the sleep you actually got as a share of what your body needed, so it's a duration score, not a quality score. Your 86% comes from sleeping 6.7 hours, well short of your sleep need of 7.8 hours — nothing more mysterious than that. One caveat: your tracker grades last night's duration at medium confidence, so read the exact minutes loosely even though the overall picture is clear. And it is a picture, not a blip — your 7-day average of 7.1 hours tells the same story of running a little lean. If you want the number to move, it responds to exactly one thing: more time in bed, added at the front of the night.",
